<p>Iranian-backed Houthi authorities detained about 20 United Nations employees in Yemen’s capital, Sanaa, on Sunday, according to UN officials and local reports [france24.com#1][japantoday.com#1][firstpost.com#1]. The group has alleged that aid programs were being used as cover for espionage activities, claims the UN has rejected [rt.com#1]. UN officials condemned the accusations as &quot;dangerous and unacceptable&quot; and called for the immediate release of all personnel [rt.com#1]. UN staff described the detentions as a serious escalation of pressure on international organizations operating in Houthi-controlled areas [france24.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/0zNWCpqKPS-YLSNAmJuySyuBZtx8f5FnSAUgYCvRcnKSdHDjIBXSy-HZNPcnavYMze0uMD2Rd-Nk5x-gNMjPOeVszPPiCLP8ZY61BTzX7cM_ZM7tXY70BgL7VZUMgo4vnmvg5RpAmHdzZmY5AGamXv4C3sj2E-M4vWHW2SJQ4vhHAdVekcbg8oEYN_t2OEwWP1dyBncQUs9OH85DUWk' alt='Sanaa, Yemen' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Earlier raid: The detentions came a day after Houthis raided another UN facility in Sanaa and confiscated equipment, a UN official said [japantoday.com#1].</li><li>Electronics seized: During Sunday’s operation, Houthis confiscated all electronic devices, including computers and phones, from UN premises, according to reports cited by the UN [rt.com#1].</li><li>Detainee nationalities: The UN said 20 staffers held include five Yemeni nationals and 15 foreign nationals [firstpost.com#1].</li><li>Territorial control: Houthis control a large portion of Yemen, shaping access and security conditions for international organizations [rt.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>The UN is in contact with the Houthis and other parties to resolve this serious situation as swiftly as possible, end the detention of all personnel, and restore full control over its facilities in Sanaa - Jean Alam</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Houthi leadership: The movement said it dismantled a &quot;dangerous espionage network&quot; and alleged aid programs, including those run by UNICEF and the World Food Programme, were used as cover for subversive operations. (<a href='https://www.rt.com/news/626691-un-staff-detained-in-yemen/'>RT</a>)</li><li>United Nations: UN officials rejected the spying allegations as &quot;dangerous and unacceptable&quot; and demanded the release of all detained aid workers. (<a href='https://www.rt.com/news/626691-un-staff-detained-in-yemen/'>RT</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/middle-east/20251020-iranian-backed-houthis-detain-un-employees-sanaa'>Iranian-backed Houthis detain two dozen UN employees in Sanaa raid</a> - france24.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/yemen%27s-houthi-rebels-detain-20-un-employees-and-confiscate-equipment'>Yemen&#x27;s Houthi rebels detain 20 U.N. employees and confiscate equipment</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.reddit.com/r/worldnews/comments/1oax9um/yemens_houthi_rebels_detain_20_un_employees_and/'>Yemen&#x27;s Houthi rebels detain 20 UN employees and confiscate equipment</a> - reddit.com</li><li><a href='https://www.rt.com/news/626691-un-staff-detained-in-yemen/'>Houthis detain UN staff in Yemen</a> - rt.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/yemen-houthi-rebels-hold-20-staffers-hostage-says-un-13943589.html'>Yemen’s Houthi rebels hold 20 staffers hostage, says UN</a> - firstpost.com</li></ul>